{
  "stem": "71.2",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "This child could feel more than any adult.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And she saved us because we escaped from the room and we went to [INAUDIBLE] that's how we came to [INAUDIBLE] that time.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we were saved there another, another few weeks because we worked on the cemetery there.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And came-- on a Saturday they announced that complete-- that the police is already send out, and we have to go to the train.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And we would have-- we could have saved ourselves, because we were saved on an attic-- in an attic in a candy factory.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And we went out from there and went to the train.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And there was a-- there was a family there, that father was a rabbi, and one of the daughters says-- and I was the youngest from-- besides my sisters-- and she says, well, wherever Sally goes we go, too.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "She knows where to go.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And believe me I did not know where we are going.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "When we are passing the coal mines in Poland-- [INAUDIBLE], that's Silesia, I think-- they said to me, see, if we would not listen to you, we would go to Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And this way they taking out to the coal mines.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "But we did arrive in Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, on that journey.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "On that journey, we arrived to our-- we were crossing-- passing, passing the coal mines.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And then from the coal mines, we came-- we came to Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Auschwitz, yes.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I was--",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That's correct.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And when we-- when we boarded the trains, a German was-- when-- his boots with-- I don't know what you call, like a--",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "A whip.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He was just hitting his boots with the whip and says, [SPEAKING GERMAN]-- excuse me for the expression.",
      "word_count": 18
    }
  ],
